test_patch:
diff --git a/test/sql/parser/indirection.test b/test/sql/parser/indirection.test
new file mode 100644
index 000000000000..0f0a15e5959b
--- /dev/null
+++ b/test/sql/parser/indirection.test
@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@
+# name: test/sql/parser/indirection.test
+# description: Test indirection
+# group: [parser]
+
+statement ok
+PRAGMA enable_verification
+
+# . after case
+query I
+select case when true then {'a': 42} end.a;
+----
+42
+
+# brackets after ARRAY constant
+query I
+select [42][1];
+----
+42
+
+query I
+select array[42][1];
+----
+42
+
+# brackets after list comprehension
+query I
+select [a for a in [42, 84]][1];
+----
+42
+
+statement ok
+prepare v1 as select $1[1];
+
+query I
+execute v1([42]);
+----
+42
problem_statement:
struct field access after CASE statement doesn't match other struct supporting sql systems
### What happens?

Field access of `struct`s computed in a case statement doesn't seem to match any of these other systems that also support structs:

- BigQuery
- Snowflake
- Trino
- ClickHouse

All of these systems support unparenthesized syntax similar to this:

```sql
select case when true then {'a': 1} end."a";
```

whereas duckdb requires parentheses around the entire case statement to work:

```sql
select (case when true then {'a': 1} end)."a";
```

This doesn't match other similar scenarios, like arithmetic where parentheses are not required:

```
D select case when true then 1 end + 1;
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ (CASE  WHEN (CAST('t' AS BOOLEAN)) THEN (1) ELSE NULL END + 1) │
│                             int32                              │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                              2 │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### To Reproduce

```
D select case when true then {'a': 1} end."a";
Parser Error: syntax error at or near "."
LINE 1: select case when true then {'a': 1} end."a";
                                               ^
```

### OS:

Linux

### DuckDB Version:

v0.10.1-dev589 e662e1e04e

### DuckDB Client:

CLI

### Full Name:

Phillip Cloud

### Affiliation:

Voltron Data

### Have you tried this on the latest [nightly build](https://duckdb.org/docs/installation/?version=main)?

I have tested with a nightly build

### Have you tried the steps to reproduce? Do they include all relevant data and configuration? Does the issue you report still appear there?
